==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prelatize
<hw>Prel"a*tize</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To uphold or encourage
prelacy; to exercise prelatical functions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An episcopacy that began then to <qex>prelatize</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

